docker run --link redis:redis <image-name> : Running docker container with <image-name> and linking to redis container. ( redis:redis :-
                                             name of redis container:name of host that new continer is looking for)

note :- In above case, running continer will create redis host entry with it internal ip-address in to /etc/hosts folder. 

---------------------
docker-compose.yml :-
---------------------

This files consists of dictionaries ---> key, values then properties and it's values.
ex:- 
dictionary:
  key: value
  property:
    - value 
    
docker-compose up : To bring up entire application stalk metioned in docker-compose file.  
